This is the README for Encode::Detective version 0.06.

Encode::Detective is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language, a
library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document contains four
sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

Encode::Detective - guess the encoding of text

This module guesses the character set of input data. It is similar to
"Encode::Guess", but does not require a list of expected encodings.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following websites:

    * http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?Encode::Detective
    * http://metacpan.org/release/Encode-Detective

(These links go to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your computer
using

    perldoc Encode::Detective

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan Encode::Detective

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm Encode::Detective

To install the module from the source file, Encode-Detective-0.05.tar.gz,
follow this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz Encode-Detective-0.05.tar.gz
    cd Encode-Detective-0.05
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can report a
bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/Encode-Detective/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of Encode::Detective, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/Encode-Detective>. 

